distance of mussel band revised post-sampling based on map. Quad sampled off tx. With gaps, mussels extend to 8.3m This interpretation of the gap rule was used often, but not by all observers. The length of each segment of continuous mussels was summed and the random proportion multiplied by that value. The resulting quad position was placed that many meters into the mussels only- sometimes the observer recorded the absolute value- number of meters from the horizontal- and sometimes not. the value from the horizontal is what is recorded in the quad/core position, but at times is impossible to determine. quad/core sample outside bed area based on gap rule.

in 2014 we sampled using the plate end as 0m so all the random vert tx distances went from the end rather than the rebar beginning.
